lead_paragraph: An Air Force Reserve rescue plane on a training mission with 11 people on board crashed into the Pacific Ocean on Friday night, and the Coast Guard today pulled one survivor and two bodies from the water. The HC-130 Hercules went down about 40 miles off Cape Mendocino in northern California after the crew reported that one of the four propeller engines had shut down and that they were having trouble with another, said Col. Rick Davis, the commander of the 939th Rescue Wing's 304th Rescue Squadron in Portland, Ore., where the plane was based.
abstract: Air Force Reserve rescue plane on training mission with 11 people on board crashes into Pacific Ocean off Cape Mendocino in northern California; Coast Guard pulls one survivor and two bodies from water (S)

headline.main: Air Force Plane Goes Down In Pacific With 11 on Board
